{
    "name": "Psychic Lich",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> any<br/><b>Organization</b> solitary<br/><b>Treasure</b> NPC gear (sickle, <i>cloak of resistance +2</i>, <i>headband of vast intelligence +2</i> [Stealth], <i>ring of counterspells</i> [<i>dispel magic</i>], <i>ring of protection +1</i>, <i>robe of blending</i>, <i>scroll of invisibility</i>, other treasure)"
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "While some liches prefer to spend undeath\u2019s eternity in seclusion, a psychic lich sustains its life force by embracing its personal accomplishments to create a powerful astral echo of itself. Even more megalomaniacal than most liches, psychic liches resemble ordinary liches for the most part, but their every moment is attended by ghostly images of past cruelties, a constantly rotating illusory display of the evil deeds that brought them their power. Most psychic liches are humans, or come from other races renowned for their psychic abilities."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>This gaunt, ghoulish figure\u2019s skin is inscribed with faintly glowing runes. Short-lived afterimages trail behind it.</i>",
